This paper focuses on the analysis of a large-scale directed network from Tumblr, which is a social media platform. The paper investigates the time delay in reciprocal relations and proposes a learning model to predict the delay. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Societal Computing). Additionally, the paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and deep learning (cs.DL) techniques for delay prediction. Finally, the paper presents experimental results to validate the proposed model, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
